Page-Bound Epiphany					TYPE:Arcane.Divine	CLASSES:Bard,Cleric,Magus,Sorcerer,Wizard=2				SCHOOL:Divination												COMPS:V,S,F	CASTTIME:1 round			RANGE:Personal	TARGETAREA:You					DURATION:(CASTERLEVEL) rounds (see text)														SOURCEPAGE:p.10	DESC:You magically scour the world's libraries for information that might refresh your memory about a topic. Upon casting this spell, the focus book's pages fill with snippets and selections from countless books. You can spend up to %1 rounds. You may cease reading at any time, and when you do you can immediately attempt one Knowledge check with a +1 circumstance bonus for each round you spent studying the book. The writing disappears when the spell ends, and if you fail to succeed at a Knowledge check on the round you stop reading the notes, you don't gain the benefits of this spell.|min(10,CASTERLEVEL)
Sure Casting						TYPE:Arcane.Divine	CLASSES:Bard,Cleric,Inquisitor,Sorcerer,Witch,Wizard=1		SCHOOL:Divination												COMPS:V,F	CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:Personal	TARGETAREA:You					DURATION:1 round (see text)																SOURCEPAGE:p.13	DESC:You gain temporary insight into your enemies' magical defenses. When you next cast a spell before the end of the next round, treat your caster level as 5 higher than normal for the purpose of overcoming spell resistance. This bonus doesn't increase any other effects that depend on caster level, such as the spell's damage or range, and affects only the first spell cast after sure casting.
